[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cardiff Celsa Steel explosion deaths inquest opened

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An inquest into the deaths of two men who died in an explosion at a Cardiff steelworks has been opened and adjourned.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Peter O'Brien, 51, from Llanishen, Cardiff, and Mark Sim, 41, of Caldicot, Monmouthshire, were killed in the blast at Celsa Steel on 18 November.
The Cardiff inquest heard Mr O'Brien was an electrical engineer while Mr Sim was a mechanical engineer.
A pre-inquest review will take place in March 2016, following an investigation.
